Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.63,0:00:45.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.21,0:00:48.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:00:54.35,Main,,0,0,0,,One bear successfully eliminated by our trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.35,0:00:57.27,Main,,0,0,0,,We know what you two really are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:06.57,Main,,0,0,0,,We hated you from the beginning--\Nand loved you from the beginning, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.57,0:01:10.28,Main,,0,0,0,,And so we wanted to\Nbecome true friends with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:15.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I wanted to cross the wall\Nand have you all to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.08,0:01:23.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Sumika, what was it you wanted to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.25,0:01:29.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Yurikumaaaaaaaaa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.30,0:01:31.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Yurikuma Arashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.89,0:03:05.06,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"One Month Ago・(History)"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.31,0:03:12.90,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a hard letter... Where should I start?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.32,0:03:23.41,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget the day I met you, Kureha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:25.96,Main,,0,0,0,,"Flashback"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.67,0:03:31.46,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"After the Entrance Ceremony・(History)"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.09,0:03:38.22,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not here... not here... What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:46.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Grandma gave it to me especially for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.35,0:03:49.85,Main,,0,0,0,,I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.85,0:03:51.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.69,0:03:56.36,Main,,0,0,0,,This is it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.95,0:03:59.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.07,0:04:10.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I know you might not even remember\Nthat, but it made me really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.71,0:04:12.29,Main,,0,0,0,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.59,0:04:14.29,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"Stormy Night・(History)"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.00,0:04:20.01,Main,,0,0,0,,I wanted to protect what you cared about, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.97,0:04:26.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.85,0:04:34.11,Main,,0,0,0,,We got soaked, remember? It was scary, but fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.11,0:04:37.49,Main,,0,0,0,,You felt so close to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.49,0:04:42.24,Main,,0,0,0,,I felt like we were the only\Ntwo people in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.24,0:04:48.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I was in heaven.\NI remember everything about that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.91,0:04:53.75,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget, even when I'm old and gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.76,0:05:03.55,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Moon Girl and the Forest Girl"...\NYour mother wrote this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.55,0:05:06.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Yep. This was her last work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.72,0:05:11.19,Main,,0,0,0,,It was never published,\Nso this is the only copy in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.19,0:05:12.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Can I read it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:13.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.78,0:05:23.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time, the worlds\Nwere divided in two by the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:26.87,Main,,0,0,0,,There was the moon world and the forest world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:34.92,Main,,0,0,0,,One day, a moon girl dropped her\Nmother's precious pendant into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.92,0:05:39.46,Main,,0,0,0,,It was a forest girl who found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:47.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Surprised by its sparkling star,\Nshe found herself looking up at the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:55.06,Main,,0,0,0,,"There must be a wonderful world\Nbeyond that sky," she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.31,0:06:02.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the moon girl couldn't stop\Nthinking about the forest world, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.70,0:06:11.12,Main,,0,0,0,,"Where is Mother's pendant?"\Nshe said. "I must go find it."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.12,0:06:19.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Day after day, the moon girl\Nand the forest girl gazed at the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.09,0:06:27.14,Main,,0,0,0,,At long last, they appealed\Nto Kumaria, the goddess of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.14,0:06:33.85,Main,,0,0,0,,The moon girl prayed,\N"Lady Kumaria, I want to go beyond the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.85,0:06:37.61,Main,,0,0,0,,and find my mother's pendant."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.61,0:06:42.61,Main,,0,0,0,,The forest girl prayed,\N"Lady Kumaria, I want to go beyond the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:47.99,Main,,0,0,0,,and deliver this star to\Nthe one who dropped it."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.99,0:06:55.42,Main,,0,0,0,,"You may not," said Kumaria,\N"for the two worlds are severed."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:07:00.42,Main,,0,0,0,,"Wanting to cross that\Nseverance is pride--a grave sin."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:02.71,Main,,0,0,0,,And yet they prayed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.71,0:07:07.13,Main,,0,0,0,,"We still want to go beyond the sky."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.13,0:07:10.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Reluctantly, Kumaria answered them:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:16.27,Main,,0,0,0,,"There is one way to make your wish come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.27,0:07:21.19,Main,,0,0,0,,In the center of the sky, there is a\Nplace called the Door to Friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:29.74,Main,,0,0,0,,If your love is true, your friend will\Nbe waiting for you on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:33.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Give her a Promise Kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.62,0:07:37.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Do that, and your wish shall come true."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.67,0:07:45.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Kumaria asked the two girls,\N"Is your love the real thing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.34,0:07:52.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Then she laid down a ladder for the girls,\Nconnecting the two worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.18,0:07:57.19,Main,,0,0,0,,And when they finally arrived\Nat the center of the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:04.44,Main,,0,0,0,,A single, vast mirror stood\Nlike a wall in their path.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:08.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Each girl saw her own reflection in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.49,0:08:12.74,Main,,0,0,0,,They heard Kumaria's voice say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.74,0:08:18.33,Main,,0,0,0,,"Now, your friend is waiting\Non the other side of that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:23.09,Main,,0,0,0,,If you smash the 'you' in the\Nmirror to bits, if you tear it apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:26.63,Main,,0,0,0,,she shall grant you a Promise Kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.63,0:08:31.39,Main,,0,0,0,,But beware: this may cost you your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:37.73,Main,,0,0,0,,I will ask you one more time:\NIs your love the real thing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.73,0:08:42.77,Main,,0,0,0,,The girls stared at themselves in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:47.49,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.49,0:08:49.86,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not the end, but it's all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.86,0:08:53.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Mom was killed by a bear\Nbefore she finished the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.91,0:08:55.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:09:02.33,Main,,0,0,0,,So, what would you do, Sumika?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.33,0:09:07.25,Main,,0,0,0,,At the end of the story.\NWould you risk your life to break the mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:10.59,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:12.26,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:17.85,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd shoot myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.31,0:09:26.73,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd shoot, and prove my love was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:34.24,Main,,0,0,0,,So I decided in that moment\Nthat I won't back down on love, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.24,0:09:36.58,Main,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.83,0:09:45.29,MainTop,,0,0,0,,Now, let's decide on the next evil to exclude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:48.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's search evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.98,0:10:05.69,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"The Invisible Storm・(Exclusion)"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:10.15,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"3."\N"4. Saori Shimabukuro"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.15,0:10:11.32,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"2."\N"3. Aoi Uezu"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:13.57,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"1."\N"2. Karen Tanaka"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:14.99,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"1. Evil = Kureha Tsubaki"\N"2. Karen Tanaka"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.99,0:10:15.82,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"Vote Not Unanimous"\N"2. Karen Tanaka"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.78,0:10:21.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Friends, we have a traitor among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.91,0:10:25.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha Tsubaki was set to be the next evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:26.13,Main,,0,0,0,,"Sumika Izumino"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.13,0:10:29.80,Main,,0,0,0,,But before that happens,\Nwe must exclude the traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.80,0:10:31.09,Main,,0,0,0,,"Sumika Izumino"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.59,0:10:34.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Sumika Izumino?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.22,0:10:38.43,Main,,0,0,0,,"Sumika Izumino"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.10,0:10:45.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha, I jumped into the storm willingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:54.32,Main,,0,0,0,,At the time, I thought that\Nif I could prove my love,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:54.74,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday Kureha"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:59.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't mind getting hurt, even heartbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:06.42,Main,,0,0,0,,But then I realized: It's not me\Nthe Invisible Storm will break.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.42,0:11:11.75,Main,,0,0,0,,It's you, the one I care about most.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.55,0:11:18.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Good, you wrote the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:21.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Harishima...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:25.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Okay, I'll give it to Tsubaki--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.19,0:11:28.90,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:33.07,Main,,0,0,0,,About the letter...\NWould you mind waiting a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.07,0:11:39.07,Main,,0,0,0,,I want you to wait until we\Ncelebrate Kureha's birthday here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:40.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.91,0:11:43.66,Main,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.66,0:11:48.25,Main,,0,0,0,,But don't forget, I'm going\Nto be Tsubaki's new friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.25,0:11:52.75,Main,,0,0,0,,That way the storm will pass her by.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.75,0:11:59.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't stop the storm; but I {\i1}can{\i0}\Nprotect Tsubaki, as her new friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.39,0:12:05.89,Main,,0,0,0,,I know it forces a terrible choice on you,\Nbut there's no other way to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.73,0:12:14.23,Main,,0,0,0,,I think I should deliver that letter after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.23,0:12:22.24,Main,,0,0,0,,No. This is the last love\NI can give her, so I'll do it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.24,0:12:24.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:27.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Harishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:28.66,Main,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:40.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha, this is my present. You see, I know now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:53.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't back down on love.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.08,0:13:06.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.62,0:13:14.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Since you told me that Ginko Yurishiro\Nand Lulu Yurigasaki were really bears,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:18.01,Main,,0,0,0,,I got to set a trap in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.01,0:13:19.42,Main,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:21.38,Main,,0,0,0,,"Flashback"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.64,Main,,0,0,0,,We know what you two really are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.56,0:13:29.77,MainTop,,0,0,0,,Bear Flash!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.69,0:13:38.07,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't believe that stupid {\i1}bear{\i0}\Nhad a trick like that up her sleeve!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.07,0:13:41.15,Main,,0,0,0,,But the plan is going without a hitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.15,0:13:48.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Sumika Izumino's death was unexpected,\Nbut your idea of {\i1}using {\i0}it was genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:54.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow it'll finally be\NKureha Tsubaki's birthday. Let's enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.55,0:14:02.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.59,0:14:05.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me they...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.64,0:14:08.31,Main,,0,0,0,,"Flashback"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:11.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Just leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.27,0:14:19.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Where'd they go? I was planning to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.11,0:14:23.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Growl... Ginko...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.70,0:14:26.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Ginko, hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:28.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Growl-sniffle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.87,0:14:36.08,Main,,0,0,0,,How did that Harishima girl\Nknow we were bears, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:49.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Reia, this reminds me of\Nthe day I swore my love to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:56.73,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder what your daughter will\Nget from her friend on her birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.99,0:15:05.65,Main,,0,0,0,,"Flashback"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.65,0:15:07.12,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday Kureha"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:11.24,Main,,0,0,0,,It's my present to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:17.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Sumika, I promise to accept your gift properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.25,0:15:23.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Tsubaki, do you remember\Nthe day of the entrance ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.59,0:15:25.05,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.05,0:15:28.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Pummeled by the cold wind\Nthat scattered the cherry blossoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.55,0:15:32.56,Main,,0,0,0,,a girl searched for something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.31,0:15:36.77,Main,,0,0,0,,It was Izumino.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.77,0:15:39.15,Main,,0,0,0,,No one helped her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.15,0:15:44.24,Main,,0,0,0,,And why would they?\NIt was just some cheap hairpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.24,0:15:46.78,Main,,0,0,0,,But you were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.28,0:15:54.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Tell me, why haven't you lost hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.75,0:15:59.42,Main,,0,0,0,,The world is so cruel. You've lost things,\Nhad them taken from you--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.42,0:16:01.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Why don't you become invisible?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.29,0:16:03.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:06.26,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it's because I don't forget love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.26,0:16:09.09,Main,,0,0,0,,You "don't forget love"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.09,0:16:13.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Right. As long as you don't\Nforget love, you'll never be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:15.39,Main,,0,0,0,,If you don't give up on love,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.39,0:16:18.44,Main,,0,0,0,,even if you lose something,\Nyou'll never be invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.85,0:16:21.44,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:25.86,Main,,0,0,0,,A letter from Sumika.\NShe gave it to me not too long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.86,0:16:31.95,Main,,0,0,0,,She wanted me to read it today,\Non my birthday, at the flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.95,0:16:38.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Tsubaki, thank you for giving us\Nthe chance to atone for our mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:41.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I look forward to your birthday party!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:42.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.79,0:16:45.63,Main,,0,0,0,,No, no need to thank me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:51.72,Main,,0,0,0,,After all, your love is about to\Nbe destroyed by the Invisible Storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.72,0:16:54.64,Main,,0,0,0,,The lily opens!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:16:56.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.68,0:17:01.15,Main,,0,0,0,,--Growl! Ginko's alive!\N--Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.15,0:17:07.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad! I didn't know\Nwhat I'd do if you died!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.32,0:17:09.40,Main,,0,0,0,,I worked really hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.40,0:17:14.24,Main,,0,0,0,,I carried you here and stayed up\Nall night taking care of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:17.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Today is Kureha's birthday! Growl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:18.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.45,0:17:20.91,Main,,0,0,0,,I said, today is Kureha's--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.75,0:17:23.71,Main,,0,0,0,,"Incoming Call: Blocked Number"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:27.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.21,0:17:29.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Is your love the real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.76,0:17:32.68,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a challenge from the Wall of Severance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.68,0:17:38.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Ginko Yurishiro, if your love\Nis true, go to the flowerbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.60,0:17:41.85,Main,,0,0,0,,The moon girl is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.85,0:17:43.77,Main,,0,0,0,,"Moon girl"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.77,0:17:48.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Give yourself over to the flames,\Nand your love will be approved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.82,0:17:52.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha! Is Kureha the moon girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.99,0:17:53.62,Main,,0,0,0,,"Blocked Number Mode"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.62,0:17:54.28,Main,,0,0,0,,"Call Ended"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.57,0:17:59.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, the question remains:\Nwill the Promise Kiss come to pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.62,0:18:04.08,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the sexy way. Shaba-da-doo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.84,0:18:09.76,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday Tsubaki"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:23.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday, Tsubaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.23,0:18:25.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.86,0:18:28.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.94,0:18:34.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Go on, you promised. Read Izumino's letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.32,0:18:35.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:46.08,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"Kureha, the girl standing\Nin front of you is your new friend"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.08,0:18:47.88,Main,,0,0,0,,What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.88,0:18:50.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Exactly what it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.42,0:18:54.55,Main,,0,0,0,,That's Sumika Izumino's breakup letter to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:55.26,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.26,0:19:03.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Her final present to you was\Na new "friend" other than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.73,0:19:07.56,Main,,0,0,0,,But we won't make friends with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.56,0:19:11.07,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, you were both tricked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.07,0:19:12.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Tricked?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.53,0:19:18.16,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right! I mean, {\i1}I'm {\i0}the one\Nwho had Sumika Izumino write that letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:24.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Her death messed up the plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:30.80,Main,,0,0,0,,but we got to use that letter to punish\Nthe real evil who can't follow social cues.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.80,0:19:36.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday, Kureha Tsubaki!\NHere's a little present from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:41.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:50.07,Main,,0,0,0,,We exclude evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.07,0:19:51.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Exclude!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:19:55.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Evil gets no friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:57.24,Main,,0,0,0,,No friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.99,0:20:02.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Evil gets crushed by the Invisible Storm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.66,0:20:04.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Crushed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.46,0:20:13.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha Tsubaki just snapped like a twig, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.55,0:20:14.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.84,0:20:16.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.38,0:20:19.89,Main,,0,0,0,,You don't get any new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.89,0:20:24.31,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't accept Sumika Izumino's final present.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.31,0:20:29.56,Main,,0,0,0,,What a pity. The emotion of\N"love" is powerless and pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:33.86,Main,,0,0,0,,No use for {\i1}this {\i0}anymore, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.86,0:20:37.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't! Sumika wrote that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.57,0:20:44.33,Main,,0,0,0,,I want you to always\Nsmile like that, like a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.33,0:20:47.83,Main,,0,0,0,,That's my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.83,0:20:51.54,Main,,0,0,0,,So I'd be happy even just\Nwatching you from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.54,0:20:54.30,Main,,0,0,0,,That's love Sumika gave to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:20:57.21,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday Kureha"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:20:59.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Growl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.68,0:21:08.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Yurishiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:16.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-The party's over, everyone! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.03,0:21:17.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.07,0:21:25.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't back down on love!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:29.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Ginko!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.42,0:21:37.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Ginko, you dummy!\NWhat if you'd really died this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.09,0:21:39.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Yurishiro, why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.59,0:21:42.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Because she loves you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.89,0:21:45.10,Main,,0,0,0,,She... loves me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.10,0:21:48.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes! Ginko loves you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.60,0:21:49.98,Main,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.90,0:21:58.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't waste her love!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.90,0:22:08.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Kureha, the girl standing\Nin front of you is your new friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.00,0:22:17.09,Main,,0,0,0,,My... friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.31,0:23:51.72,MainTop,,0,0,0,,"That Fateful Morning・(History)"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.77,0:23:57.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm a little early?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:24:04.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Still, I need to make this place full\Nof flowers again by Kureha's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.69,0:24:07.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Izumino!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.74,0:24:13.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.16,0:24:14.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Bear shock!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.54,0:24:18.50,Main,,0,0,0,,It's such a nice morning. And I'm starving!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.50,0:24:20.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Yurizono...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.09,0:24:27.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Chomp, chomp, grawr. Chomp, chomp, grawr.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.05,0:24:30.55,Main,,0,0,0,,That day, I committed a serious crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.55,0:24:32.97,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm a criminal-bear.
